body:
I think this logic doesn't match the BIP, as it currently implements "all outputs have to be taproot outputs" rather than "at least _one_ output has to be a taproot output"? Could use `std::none_of` to achieve the latter (https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/algorithm/all_any_none_of).

Something like
```
    if (std::none_of(tx.vout.begin(), tx.vout.end(), [](const TxOut& txout) {
            std::vector<std::vector<unsigned char>> solutions;
            return Solver(vout.scriptPubKey, solutions) == TxoutType::WITNESS_V1_TAPROOT;
        }) {
        return false;
    }
```
(untested)

